{"article_id":"YnMIBvzsIhlmMl0y","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"By a 54-41 percent margin , American voters would get rid of the sweeping 2010 health care law","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"if given the option ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"according to a new poll .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"The poll ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"released Wednesday ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"also shows","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"most voters","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"-- 71 percent --","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"think","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"the more than 15,000 pages of regulations","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"that implement the Affordable Care Act ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"popularly known as Obamacare ,","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"are \" way over the top. \"","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"Some 19 percent say","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"that number of pages \" seems about right . \"","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"The concern about the small mountain of health care rules is bipartisan .","depth":5},{"id":16,"text":"Even 56 percent of Democrats call the 15,000 pages of regulations \" way over the top , \"","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"as do 71 percent of independents and 87 percent of Republicans .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"As for the law itself , the poll asks people what they would do with it","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"if there were an up-or-down vote today .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"While a 54-percent majority would repeal the law ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"41 percent would keep it in place .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"That ' s mostly unchanged from two years ago ,","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"when 56 percent said","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"they would cancel it","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"and 39 percent wanted the law to remain","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"( January 2011 ) .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"On the law itself views are divided along partisan lines .","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"By a 48 percentage-point margin , most Democrats favor keeping Obamacare","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"( 72-24 percent ) ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"while Republicans favor repealing it by an even wider 77-point margin","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"( 87-10 percent ) .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"Independents also favor repeal , but by a narrower 16-point margin","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"( 53-37 percent ) .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Voters give President Obama negative ratings on health care .","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"By a 10-point margin , more disapprove","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"( 53 percent )","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"than approve","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"( 43 percent )","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"of his job performance .","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"That ' s the lowest rating","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"he ' s received on health care","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"since his 13-point negative rating in December 2011","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"( 42-55 percent ) .","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Seven percent of voters say","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"health care is the most important issue","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"facing the country ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"which puts it well behind the economy","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"( 42 percent ) ,","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"the federal deficit","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"( 17 percent )","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"and terrorism","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"( 9 percent )","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"on the priority list .","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"Health care still tops guns","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"( 5 percent ) ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Social Security","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"( 5 percent ) ,","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"immigration","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"( 4 percent )","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"and foreign policy","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"( 1 percent ) .","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"These health care poll results are based on landline and cell phone interviews with 1,009 randomly chosen registered voters nationwide .","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"The poll was conducted under the joint direction of Anderson Robbins Research","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"( D )","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"and Shaw & Company Research","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"( R )","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"from April 20 - 22 .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"The full poll has a margin of sampling error of plus or minus three percentage points .","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"Almost all voters","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"-- 85 percent --","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"say","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"it ' s okay for adults to use medical marijuana","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"if it is prescribed by a physician .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"Still , there ' s some doubt about its use :","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"The poll , finds","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"30 percent of voters think","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"people","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"who smoke medical marijuana","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"truly need it for medical purposes ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"while nearly half","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"-- 47 percent --","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"think","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"those people just want to smoke pot .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"In general , voters are about evenly divided over legalizing marijuana :","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"46 percent of voters favor legalization ,","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"while 49 oppose .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"Democrats favor the legal route by 57-39 percent ;","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"Republicans oppose it , 62-33 percent .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"These poll results on marijuana are based on landline and cell phone interviews with 1,010 randomly chosen registered voters nationwide .","depth":4},{"id":90,"text":"The poll was conducted under the joint direction of Anderson Robbins Research","depth":5},{"id":91,"text":"( D )","depth":5},{"id":92,"text":"and Shaw & Company Research","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"( R )","depth":6},{"i